cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with M2M traffic in an industrial automation scenario, which involves networking and communication aspects. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a multi-class scheduler to manage the heterogeneous M2M traffic, which involves control and management of systems. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the delay-performance of the M2M uplink channel and proposes a mapping of delay requirements using step and sigmoidal functions, which involves information theory concepts. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a scheduler to manage the traffic at the PLC, which involves distributed computing aspects. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the classification of M2M traffic into Event Driven and Periodic Update data, which can be considered as multimedia data.
